title: Useless Movement EP; audiophile vinyl rip, Terre Thaemlitz
description:
This is deep house music, experimental, repetitive and probably best (if not only) listened to with an altered mind, unless you REALLY are into this sort of thing. You have been warned. 

What is more remarkable however was that it was transcribed using a $30,000 SME30 turntable, Graham 2.2 tonearm, Jan Allaerts cartridge and a $15,000 custom all-tube phono stage
